               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Būstān by Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2002005579" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_908-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian </textLang>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_8149912313906210668">Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_8149912313906210668">تميز الدّين ابن محمّد ياور</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_23207">Būstān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_23207">بوستان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Autograph copy of a lexicon or farhang and commentary or sharḥ by <persName key="viaf_8149912313906210668" role="aut scr">Mawlavī Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar</persName> appended in margins around the bi-columnar arrangement of the mas̲navī, the <title key="work_23207">Būstān</title> of <persName key="person_100206721" role="ant">Shaykh Saʿdī Shīrāzī</persName>. 
                        </p>
                        <p>This copy, begun in Ramaz̤ān 1238/May 1823, was intended for lithography. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 115r): completed probably in the hand of the author (Tamīz al-Dīn ibn Muḥammad Yāvar), for the <orgName>Maṭbaʿ Aysiyātik Līthūgrāfik Kanpī</orgName> (sic, <orgName>Asiatic Lithographic Company</orgName>), dār al-ḥukūmat <placeName>Calcutta</placeName>, 1244/1828. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Minute scribal nastaʿlīq, arranged in three vertical columns and a lower panel, two vertical columns for the Būstān, the third vertical column and the lower panel reserved for the lexicon and commentary. 
</p>
                        <p>Verses counted in accordance with the chapters or bāb. 
</p>
                        <p>Paginated in Persian, with stamped foliation. 
</p>
                        <p>Original covers lost. 
</p>
                        <p>Only front board remaining from later tooled leather covers (board delaminating revealing Kaithi accounts). 
</p>
                     </note>
